data.name: Almond Joy Waffles
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously chocolatey waffles topped with almond slices and coconut flakes, inspired by the classic candy bar!
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your waffle maker according to the manufacturer's instructions.
In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa powder, and sugar until well combined.
In another bowl, mix the milk, eggs, and melted butter until smooth.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Gently fold in the chocolate chips.
Spray the waffle maker with non-stick cooking spray. Pour the batter into the waffle maker, close the lid, and cook until the waffles are crispy, about 5-7 minutes.
Serve the waffles warm, topped with sliced almonds, shredded coconut, and a drizzle of chocolate syrup if desired.
